From The Tiffany Archives
-
A century-old symbol of courage, preserved in The Tiffany Archives forever. In 1912, this Tiffany & Co. 18k gold pocket watch was given as a tribute to Captain Arthur Rostron, whose swift action aboard the R.M.S. Carpathia saved nearly 700 lives in the aftermath of the R.M.S. Titanic. More than a timepiece, it is a timeless expression of gratitude and a remarkable chapter in the House's storied legacy.

#TiffanyAndCo #TiffanyWatches

From The Tiffany Archives
-
In 1887, Tiffany & Co. secured nearly one third of the French Crown Jewels at auction—a bold move sparked by founder Charles Lewis Tiffany's audacious spirit. This defining moment not only reshaped the House's legacy but also cemented its reputation as a global high jeweler and force to be reckoned with. Today, a selection of these storied jewels continue to inspire from their place in The Tiffany Archives as a testament to the House's enduring legacy of daring innovation.

#TiffanyAndCo
